title: Quadrants
text: We know that the quadrants have angles $$0$$ to $$90$$ degress or $$\frac{\pi}{2}$$ radians for Q1, $$90$$ to $$180$$ degrees of $$\frac{\pi}{2}$$ to pi radians for Q2 and so on. We just need the actual angle to be between $$0$$ and $$360$$ degress or $$2\pi$$ radians to find its quadrant.
